column18: 10/2/2000: Assailants threw bricks and then firebombs at a synagogue in Dusseldorf, Germany.  No one was injured in the attack and a neighbor who witnessed the attack climbed the perimeter fence and put out the flames before any major damage occurred.  Witnesses stated that the attack was perpetrated by at least two assailants; two 15-year-old young men were taken into custody.  The attack occurred the night before the ten year anniversary of Germany's unity.
